tand better the trajectories of this most important ancient art form, The Music of Tragedy argues, we must pay closer attention to the role played by both music and text.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aGreek drama (Tragedy)xHistory and criticism. 0aMusic, Greek and RomanxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aancient art form.  aancient poetry.  aclassic poetry.  aclassical greek theater.  adrama.  adramatic plot.  adramaturgical effects.  aeuripides.  aexperimentation.  aimagery.  ameta theatrical flourishes.  amotifs.  amousike.  amusic making.  amusic.  amusical language.  anovelty.  aperformance.  areligious practices.  atraditional lyrics styles.  atragic dramas and plays.  atragic stage.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831106675540 cprintz978052029590240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520968493423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520968493/original  a978-3-11-066755-4  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY